Sentencas: Calcium and strontium-doped praseodymium manganite powders were prepared as cathode materials in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Characteristics of Pr1-xMxMnO3 (M=Ca, Sr) as cathode material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The characteristics of these materials such as particle size distribution, electrical conductivity, cathodic polarization, thermal expansion, and reactivity with electrolyte were investigated.
Titulo: Characteristics of Pr1-xMxMnO3 (M=Ca, Sr) as cathode material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was found that the optimum doping content of Ca and Sr was 30 mol% and that Ca-doped PrMnO3 had higher electrical conductivity and lower cathodic overpotential than Sr-doped PrMnO3.
Titulo: Characteristics of Pr1-xMxMnO3 (M=Ca, Sr) as cathode material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Further, the 30 mol% Ca-doped PrMnO3 had not reacted with Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) in the temperature range 1000-1200 degrees C for 100 h and it had a thermal expansion coefficient close to that of YSZ.
Titulo: Characteristics of Pr1-xMxMnO3 (M=Ca, Sr) as cathode material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was found that 30 mol% Ca-doped PrMnO3 was satisfactory for use as a cathode material in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Characteristics of Pr1-xMxMnO3 (M=Ca, Sr) as cathode material in solid oxide fuel cells
